text:
a friend of mine was recently violated. a friend of mine went on a date and trusted she would make it home safe; she believed a man who promised to keep his distance. a friend of mine was wrong. a friend of mine struggled and fought for 40 minutes before she was finally able to escape. a friend of mine blames herself for all the wrong reasons. a friend of mine is struggling with depression and anxiety as her body processes the trauma and as the criminal justice system processes her. a friend of mine is using the punishing winds of winter hikes to externalize all the pain and anger inside. a friend of mine was raped. and she wishes coming out as a survivor was as easy as coming outdoors for healing.
.
to all you silent warriors out there, keep fighting. we will know your name by the defiance in your strut.
.
.
note: the panunkey, piscataway, and other #native tribes originally lived in and traveled through the land that is now rock creek national park. .
.

text:
we want to achieve a safe place for those, past and present, who have been affected by assault and harassment, directly and indirectly. we want people to know we are there if they want any kind of support that is not of an authoritive figure, to talk and give advice to people regarding their situations or simply just be friends. there is no pressure to talk about anything that you do not feel comfortable talking about. 
not everyone is lucky enough to know someone who has been through a similar situation, who can give advice and emotional support, so this group offers that both online and in person.

myself and sister queen @jillxfx have joined forces to raise awareness about rape, abuse and the prejudices surrounding it.  we would love it if our pageant family could take part.  if you would like to then take a photo in black and white with your mascara smudged either holding a white piece of paper or write â€œ.... is not consentâ€ on yourself.  you may chose the first part â€œie marriage is not consentâ€, â€œdating is not consentâ€ etc etc.  please tag both myself and jill in the post along with the hashtags 
#thisisnotconsent #crownsforacause #sisterqueensagainstsilence 
anyone can join in, male or female as this isnâ€™t just something that affects women. 
i also have the following video i made 9 years ago if you would like to take a look:

an invitation to the christmas party is key here â€“ an invitation, rather than an expectation. for the most part, people will joyfully accept. but for those who donâ€™t, theyâ€™ll appreciate your understanding and not being labelled a scrooge!

text:
many people on here know that in feb. of this year i was physically assaulted by someone i loved and trusted, who was twice my size. what many people donâ€™t know isâ€”in the process of doing what i thought and still believe was right (leaving his ass and reporting him), i became a wanted person in the eyes of nypd. this isnâ€™t about airing dirty laundry. this is about having a voice.
.
earlier this year, in april, i was arrested as a result of retaliation by my assaulter. recently, i got my release papers framed as an overall â€œfuck youâ€ to the system and a reminder to myself of how much iâ€™ve grown and learned (and continue to!) since the assault and arrest, thanks to an amazing support system (love yâ€™all).
.
.
there arenâ€™t many things more frightening than the cops calling you threatening felony charges, threatening to issue an arrest and search warrant, overstepping your constitutional rights, and demanding that you go â€œseeâ€ them. all while still having bruises on my arms and ribs (other body parts had since healed).
.
.
from first hand experience, i can tell you that we as a society still have a long way to go in terms of how we treat victims of all kinds who come forward. also bear with me as i have a pop culture moment and take this time to say fuck da police - the traumas you gave me have only made me stronger.
.
.
thank you for coming to my ted talk i am here to answer any questions and sadly no i do not have a copy of my mugshot <3
.
#metoo #believesurvivors #fuckthepolice

text:
a 17 year old rape victim lost her case in court, after a lawyer used her lace underwear to argue that she consented to sex. 
a similar case took place in 2002, where lindsay armstrong committed suicide, after the court made her hold up her underwear three times, which had â€œlittle devilâ€ written across it, arguing that the style of the underwear proved consensual sex.

the sad part about rape, is that the victims feel more shame than the offender. 
linda armstrong, lindsayâ€™s mother, stated â€œshe felt she had been raped all over again during a trial that had left her humiliated and degraded.â€ underwear choice is not consent. 
clothing choice is not consent. 
1/5 womenâ€™s and 1/71 men, will be raped at some point in their lives. 
51.1 % of female victims of rape reported being raped by an intimate partner and 40.8 % by an acquaintance.
in 8/10 cases of rape, the victim knew the perpetrator.

text:
selfcare comes in many shapes. sometimes, it's taking a bath; it can be having some alone time, reading a book, watching a film or it can be buying flowers for yourself. i do take a lot of selfcare lately - if you don't take good care of yourself, who else does?
this time, i'm going on holidays in the netherlands and i'm going to do something really crazy there. probably the craziest thing i've done in years. after all the struggles of the last years, i want to feel comfortable and empowered in my body. i don't want it to be only a shell, but a home again - and that needs a peace contract, a reminder for myself which i can turn to whenever i need it. that's why i finally fulfilled myself a pretty private wish and booked a lingerie shooting with @josefienhoekstra. i really admire her work and am really looking forward to the shoot and the results. (because lingerie is not consent, neither meant for male gaze - it's meant to empower women.) i combine this adventure with some days in amsterdam; spending some days abroad is truly freeing. are there places you can recommend? i want to see the most beautiful places and create a wonderful impression of this whole trip. :)

text:
iâ€™m asked every day â€œhow do i become a hackerâ€ . i tell people that the only way to learn to break shit is to actually get in and break it.

thereâ€™s no secret book or course that will give you hacker instincts. there are a lot of hackers out there. some are versatile enough to be useful on a project, most are not.  as for the most dangerous in this realm? without a doubt, steer clear of the social engineer with technical acumen and a vendetta.

why? because with only your last name and a general idea of where you have been in the last 30 days, i can wreak havoc so potent and so severe and from so many directions you have no chance of ever rebounding once i sink my talons into you.

start with osint, then move to script kiddie exploits, then experiment with customizing exploits that are surgically targeted. social engineering helps you zero in on and manipulate the target, technical prowess helps customize the exploits. 
who will hire you? check out law firms, security firms and contract firms that work with federal agencies.

text:
here is a "positives" update:
- i am so thankful for all of the love and support i have been receiving through out my mental health recovery. - i absolutely love my job as a senior care manager. - wanda and i are moving out with roommates at the beginning of next week and i am super excited! - i am so grateful for my cat. she helps calm me when i need it. - i am super grateful for my sisters, brother in law, my boyfriend, my aunt (@travelqueen007 ), my nieces, and my closest friends. i wouldn't have been able to make it this far in life without them and i appreciate and love them more than i can put into words. 
i hope everyone is having a wonderful day!ğŸ’—

text:
this weekâ€™s wic wednesday is christine wilson, our shelter manager at marianneâ€™s place!

how did you get involved with wic? 
i started volunteering with wic, got to know the agency and within the year i got hired on as relief staff for the shelter. i went from relief to team lead and after about 10 years of that i went into the volunteer coordinator role. i took a year off because i had my daughter then i came back for a two years and continued as the volunteer manager until the current shelter manager left. after that i put my name in the hat for the residential manager and have been here every since, which has been about 12 years.
.
.
what changes have you seen during your time with wic?
the world has changed and by reflection weâ€™ve seen how the work has changed. how information is so at your fingertips now, the pervasive needs that people have around supports. everybody is dealing with so many different barriers because system navigation has been even more difficult and more of a struggle. even things like the #metoo movement, conversations are happening now that weâ€™ve known for a while. itâ€™s a bit validating that we arenâ€™t alone in this fight anymore. .
.
what do you do outside of work?
raise a couple kids, one is a teenager. but what i do for fun is i usually play some sort of sport. i play ball hockey in the winter and spring and then softball in the summer. my partner and i do renovations on our own house so we usually have an ongoing project. in the summer, we go camping, thatâ€™s a huge part. i try and do stuff in the winter like skating, skiing with the kids.
.
.
what would you say to someone about to donate to wic?
theyâ€™re helping woman and their kids leave violence and have a chance and a safer start. sometimes the donation doesnâ€™t always have to be big, it doesnâ€™t have to be money, sometimes those in-kind donations can go a long way. itâ€™s about feeling like youâ€™re a part of the solution. when youâ€™re volunteering or donating places, itâ€™s your chance to make a positive in this world.

hear me too ! 
our voices and stories must be heard. 
one in three women experience violence in their lifetime, across all social status, class, race, country or age group. thatâ€™s one too many. for many of them, the #metoo moment hasnâ€™t come yet, because speaking out can have fatal consequences, and survival is a long and complicated journey.
join us on november 22 at the assembly hall lawns for our clothes line project as we recognize the international day for the elimination of violence against women

text:
i am not a shining example of healing.
i am not well adjusted.
i am not ok a decent portion of the time.
i havenâ€™t always done the best i could but iâ€™m working towards that.
.
i buried it for years. i let it eat a part of me away. i didnâ€™t speak up.
.
i only started taking medication that iâ€™ve probably needed for most of my life a few months ago and itâ€™s like iâ€™d been living my life as a clenched fist and the grip is finally starting to loosen.
.
i could say that i donâ€™t regret it because regret is useless but i do and iâ€™ve been beating myself up about not starting meds sooner. i know i donâ€™t have to feel shame but those feelings of regret are part of the process whether or not theyâ€™re feelings i should or shouldnâ€™t have.
.
i am still learning to carry this. i am still a work in progress. iâ€™ll never stop being a work in progress because there is no tangible finish line to healing.
.
iâ€™m not a good example of someone who came out the other side stronger. but i am strong. anyone who is a survivor of trauma, sexual or otherwise, is strong for surviving but itâ€™s not the source of our strength.
.
i was always strong but strength doesnâ€™t always help you get through. itâ€™s not always enough. and thatâ€™s ok.
.
asking for help and accepting it donâ€™t diminish your strength, they help you reinforce the strength you already have. healing is messy. recovery isnâ€™t perfect. and you donâ€™t have to do it alone.
.
you are enough. mess and all.
.

text:
i'm only a dm or email away. .
.
for those in the us (or other places where thanksgiving traditions and timing are a factor), the next few days can be filled with a variety of triggers and traumas - and the general stresses of holidays can make everything we're already struggling with feel worse.
.
.
the beautiful souls who lead in this space have given of their time and expertise, to provide specific resources for nagivating the many challenges of the next few days. these are powerful, valuable reminders for all of us, regardless of the season.
.
.
but if you find yourself needing to vent, to unload without having to explain the details or provide back-story, to just seek some unconditional, empathetic support... i'm here. dm here or email speak@thewordforthis.com. .
.
@thewordforthis .
.
[image: light grey background with a bare, snow-covered branch. text reads "i'm here."]

it's an amazing romance and at the same time the author talks about sexual abuse and how often the victims are judged instead of the abuser. it's a harsh reality, to be a woman in such a misogynist society but the romance genre it's a safe environment for us and even if sofie has been abused she gets the happy ending that she deserves. and she falls in love with trevor, a man who respects her, cares for her and supports her. ğŸ’š

text:
all i wanted to do that day was immortalize my youth my beauty! #metoo #timesup #timesupnow
earlier this week i found myself sobbing uncontrollably! it hit me like a freight train as i thought back over the course of my life the times i had been sexually harassed, sexually abused, and sexually assaulted most by men i knew some of whom i attended edinboro and cheyney with. people often ask why i don't have any solid professional photos and the truth is after september 2009 when i invited a photographer friend who i had known at that point for 15 years into my home  to shoot me and it turn into a sexual harassment photo session  i have  not been able to  bring myself to sit for a photographer in studio! i would make appointments with some of the best and well respected photographers in ny and cancel at the last second! i remember telling one of my college besties about what had transpired in my home the day of the shoot and she blamed me for presenting myself to him in a sexy and provocative way. "what did you expect to happen?" she said. "i mean you're walking around half naked!" my head was fucked up! but i what i have not dealt with is the trauma. the trauma of trying to reconcile whether or not i was responsible for how a man behaves towards me...... this is too much! i am drained! so basically i cannot be in a photo session alone because the photographer is going to try and fuck me. ... and whenever i hear a photographer say to me "i gotta get you in the studio" my skin crawls, my mouth drys out, my chest tightens and all i can say to myself is no motherfucker you will not get me in your studio your chambers of hell.. no you will not (to be continued)

text: i was delighted but a little confused at first about why the geniuses behind the @nytimes truth ad campaign wanted to feature our 8 spectacular pies project â€” they usually highlight the harder news coverage, trump and #metoo. but: they're geniuses. they wanted to highlight the diligence, the attention to detail, the sheer amount of work that goes into everything the times does â€” even pies. and there were dozens of ideas from @emcdowell, our writer, countless emails and phone calls and several days on set. each of our final pies was made several times over, and that doesn't even count the reject pies â€” which means that well over a hundred pies were baked in order to bring you something delicious and ingenious. then there were recipes to edit, photos to shoot, videos to produce. a lot of obscenely talented people worked on this project and i'm so proud it was chosen to be featured. and you can hear me saying "over and over" about halfway through if you listen closely enough. long live the truth, especially at 400 degrees for 40 minutes! @nytcooking #nytpies nytimes.com/pie

text:
last week, i had the honor of representing the @equalityleague's advisory council at their first reception (hence the flower in my fro) and i got to meet a whole bunch of inspiring women. the conversation of the night was about how eql is going to be one of the leading organizations in global human rights and sports.â €
â €
two women who i talked to that night really stand out to me in these pictures.â €
â €
first, nancy hogshead-makar: olympic gold medalist in swimming and sports human rights lawyer. i interviewed her at the players' tribune and it's always amazing being around her light (and her superb photo editing skills lol). she's helped to defend many athletes in the #metoo era and helped to pass the safe sport act.â €
â €
second, judge rosemarie aquilina (in the center): the judge who sentenced larry nassar in the usa gymnastics sex abuse scandal.â €
â €
i'm so grateful that i get to be surrounded by such incredible and highly influential women and men.â €
â €

text:
so i was looking to post a picture for the school, and all the skaters we had were male, and we do have a bunch of females who skate. so i started searching social media for images of females shredding. 
all but the one on the top left were simply ads of girls selling clothes holding longboards. i used it. she was strong. 
but was it the most popular because she wore a bikini top? it started a whole conversation with myself, in my head, about what objectification means in conjunction with social media in the #metoo era. 
is it victim blaming, if you shudder when you see your daughter or her friends posting pictures of themselves in bikinis? i think so. 
yet you do worry for their safety. do you worry for their reputation? for the way men they meet might prejudge them? or future employers? can they be taken seriously as intellectuals? 
you do have some of these thoughts with your son, but never about his appearance. how is this fair? how is this right? how can we move past it without discussing it? at least we are, right? #thekidsarealright

text:
editorâ€™s note:
the reason i wanted to put together this photo shoot for our body episode is because the me too movement holds a special place in my heart. women rule my life, from my mother and my sisters, my nieces and from aunts to my grandmothers, my friends and my co-workers i am surrounded by strong beautiful women. i see women as precious intelligent creators that should be held at the highest esteem. i understand and acknowledge that i am a white male and in america, being a white male, it is my responsibility to use the privilege that was forced upon me at birth for something greater. it is not enough to live in my privilege, but if i am able to take it and bestow it upon others in their time of need then i feel like i am worth more than what is seen skin deep. no one deserves to be abused in any way, especially sexually. there is not a single thing any woman or man can do to warrant sexual abuse. i have suffered my own unwarranted sexual advances and i have dealt with and have seen so much sexual abuse in my short lifetime that i need the world, everyone of all ages, races, sexuality, and gender who have been sexually abused in any way, to know that zynon stands with you, that i stand with you. you are not alone. #metoo ~ @kalobdaniel
photography by @aminaeffinshaw and @sabrinadunnephoto

text:
is the la district attorneys office protecting a man for his politics?
_____________________________________
michael avenatti (dubbed "creepy porn lawyer") escaped prosecution of the felony charges lobbied against him by a number of women he has allegedly assaulted. most recent among these women is his recently estranged wife, lisa. with multiple bruises and scrapes, it is uncountable that the woman was physically attacked. michael even admitted to the crime in his own defense statement "she hit me first". of course, i am not one to 'believe all women' but this is a case where the evidence is clear. the district attorneys attempts to downplay the scenario as a misdemeanor are indeed egregious and i would never stand by them.
_____________________________________
with evidence and this not being the first instance not withstanding, michael avenatti should be charged with a felony. the fact that the district attorneys refuse to charge him with such could really only mean one thing, they are protecting him for his role in the anti-trump movement. regardless of feeling about trump, chivalry is not dead yet. beating women is gross. it's one thing of she used lethal force or attacked you in a way that required self defense, it's an entirely other issue if you have a history of abuse and you came away without a mark.
#avenatti #trump #conservative #walkaway #freespeech #politics #political #publicsquare #metoo

text:
"kou aeap rhat mou aow" - 9x12" - oil on canvas board
.
i was going to sleep one night when out of nowhere, i had three visions within like 5 minutes. this was one of them (the other two - soon to follow). took notes...the next morning, i did extensive research on every angle of this piece to cover my ass. .
...i succeeded.
.
we've all heard that even the prison system has etiquette - they hate #rapists. and we must never forget that rape is the only crime that can never be attributed to survival. eventually the suspect becomes the victim within prison walls. karma has a face too. you reap what you sow.
.
kou aeap rhat mou aow
.
as i've mentioned before, when you paint a portrait, you really get pulled into it - hours at a time. in this case it was hell. #harveyweinstein has one of the ugliest faces i've ever seen. his eyes gave me anxiety attacks. the crevices in his skin were horrid. his lack of eyebrows creepy. but being in your comfort zone will kill you anyways.
.
.
.

text:
this i not what i normally post here, but i felt something needed to be said; rape is not about sex or love it's about power. power that's left in the hands of the accused, and this time like many others, the accuser has won. this girl was victimized in her own court hearing, "you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front" (the exact words of the judge) she was forced to hold her own underwear up for everyone to see. the case was dismissed and the accused was acquitted. now the 27 year old man will continue to walk free and the 17 year old girl who just wanted to get justice for herself, is dead. there's nothing that can be done to bring her back, no amount of social media posts or hashtags or rallies can bring her back, but it can keep her story alive. girls, boys, women and men are ashamed to go to the authorities when they experience rape or sexual assault, so many cases are dismissed and the victims are humiliated, left with nothing but their story. this is not fair. if they're not taken seriously no one will come forth and thousands of accusers will continue to walk the streets with nothing but pride and not a single punishment. don't be afraid to get help, call 911, go to the police, protect yourself so you can protect those who might have come after you.
#metoo #thisisnotconsent

text:
before i wake - watercolor - 10 x 14 inches

the title of the painting comes from a childâ€™s bedtime prayer: â€œnow i lay me down to sleep.
i pray the lord my soul to keep.
if i should die before i wake,
i pray to god my soul to take.â€ this watercolor sketch was one of the first of many attempts to paint how things change. in this sketch there is the change from interior to exteriorâ€” from the confines of the room out onto the spaces of the road and into the landscape and mountains in the distance. the little girl runs between one reality into another.

years later iâ€™m still trying to paint metaphors for change.
years later, the little girl tells me she is still running.

text: tomorrow's a funny day, the day to follow is hysterical. it's like let's be grateful for 3 hours, then violently purge consumerism the next day. i just need to say, i'm enough, good, bad, any random misplaced judgements; whatever i'm enough. can't show up to celebrations as myself, actually dressed not in pajamas semi decently in a sweater to be sent to change because my sweater is ugly. i showed up right? i hope whatever home stuff people are going through is either avoided or put down for the day. america was stolen, although togetherness days are important. it's just funny to me, how tomorrow is gratitude day. yet it seems any other day is the day to provoke losses on each other. life's not really a competition, i like what i have, and nothing else is needed. furthering advancement and accomplishments that aren't blood soaked from others means something to me. i hope tomorrow lasts, and not in ways of celebrating genocide, that's terrible. in ways of i hope we all start thankfullyliving everyday. stop roadblocking education and progress. definetly stop trying to slaughter the kids and anyone who sees enough good in you to care for a moment. real sick of being treated like kenny from south park. if someone sees the good in you, notice that's part of how they love themselves, refrain from attacking them for it, they will no longer see the good in you. see the good in the future of those child hostages. respectfully, humanely. have a happy day, however you do. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors p.s. i love my doggie friend companion homey!

i just want to take a moment to express my sincere gratitude for each and every one of you who has been a part of my journey and the evolution of cara blanchard training, inc. over the past year. i had to make some difficult decisions in changing my business in order to do what was best, and healthiest, for my horses and myself. these decisions have also allowed me to begin pursuing one of my ultimate lifelong goals of competing at the international level by purchasing fiona. the moment i saw her i knew an incredible adventure was about to happen - sheâ€™s a dream come true! this summer when i told part of steeleâ€™s story (http://carablanchardtraining.com/shame-on-you/) and received an incredible amount of support, cbt began to take the shape that i had always hoped it would. while promoting and sharing my passion for classical dressage, i am also able to speak about equine welfare and doing right by every horse. i have even shared stories about some of the abuse iâ€™ve personally endured and hopefully been able to inspire others to believe in themselves. thank you for allowing me to be a part in your journeys, iâ€™m truly humbled. please donâ€™t ever give up and always enjoy the ride! what a wonderful thought it is that some of our best days havenâ€™t even happened yet! ğŸ’

text:
khas kepada kadet badan-badan beruniform palapes, kor suksis, kor sispa dan bsmm

gangguan seksual adalah satu kesalahan!
.
.
sebarang perlakuan bersifat seksual yang menyebabkan seseorang yang waras tersinggung, terhina atau terugut boleh dikenakan tindakan tatatertib .
.
[peraturan 4a, peraturan-peraturan pegawai awam (kelakuan & tatatertib) 1993] & pekeliling perkhidmatan bil.22 tahun 2005. .
.

jika ia terjadi kepada anda bagaimana anda menangani gangguan berkenaan? .
adakah anda berdiam diri ? menjerit? pendam ? laporkan kepada pihak yang bertanggungjawab?
.
.

untuk mengetahui hal yang lebih lanjut ayuh sertai kami dalam program ini! .
.

pusat kesatria akan mengadakan program pencegahan gangguan seksual pada 19 dsember 2018 (rabu) jam 2.00 petang bertempat di dewan auditorium pusat kesatria ukm .
.

mohon 20 orang kadet setiap badan beruniform dan kakitangan palapes, kor suksis, kor sispa dan bsmm sertai kami . diutamakan kepada kadet siswi/kakitangan wanita dan dialu-alukan kepada kadet siswa/kakitangan lelaki .
.
. 
jika terdapat sebarang pertanyaan mohon hubungi pihak kami di talian 03-89214995
.
.
.

#nomeansno
#saynotoharrasment

text:
kepolisianÂ indiaÂ telah mendaftarkan sebuah kasus ke pengadilan yang melibatkan aktorÂ india,Â alok nath.Â alok nathÂ dituntut atas tuduhan pemerkosaan oleh produsernya, vinta nanda. kasusÂ alok nathÂ hanyalah satu dari segelintir kasus yang benar-benar diterima oleh kepolisian sejak munculnya gerakan #metoomovement.

kasus pemerkosaan olehÂ alok nathÂ sebelumnya dibeberkan oleh nanda melalui laman facebooknya pada bulan oktober lalu. nath sendiri membantah tuduhan tersebut dan melayangkan gugatan balasan kepada nanda. ia meminta nanda memohon maaf dan meminta kompensasi simbolis sebesar 1 rupee

tuduhan perkosaan kepadaÂ alok nathÂ tidak hanya dilayangkan oleh nanda, dikabarkan ada dua aktris lainnya yang melayangkan tuduhan serupa.

nanda terlibat dalam suatu proyek bersama nath di tahun 1990, yakni kala mereka mengerjakan serial televisi berjudul tara. nanda mengaku butuh waktu untuk mengumpulkan keberanian selama 19 tahun untuk mengungkapkan apa yang dialaminya.

dalam tulisan di laman facebooknya, nanda tidak menyebut secara spesifik siapa aktor yang ia maksud. ia baru mengakui bahwa yang ia maksud adalahÂ alok nathÂ di kemudian hari.

di sisi lain,Â alok nathÂ mengatakan bahwa ia percaya bahwa pemerkosaan telah terjadi, namun bukan ia pelakunya.

dalam beberapa bulan terakhir gerakan #metoomovement telah membesar, menumbuhkan keberanian bagi para wanita untuk mengungkapkan apa yang mereka alami. gerakan ini menyeret banyak nama, termasuk dari kalangan aktor, jurnalis, komedian, penulis, sutradara, hingga pejabat publik.

tanushree dutta adalah aktris pertama yang melaporkan pelecehan seksual yang ia alami 10 tahun lalu. pelecehan tersebut dilakukan oleh aktor yang menjadi lawan mainnya, nana patekar. sejak saat itu, para wanita memiliki keberanian untuk melaporkan pelecehan dan kekerasan seksual terhadap mereka
.
.source by : akurat .
.

text:
let's see what is this cause about.

in recent years delhi's uprising crime in terms of molestation, eve teasing, harassment, etc has been a constant issue while all the official authorities fail to make delhi safe.
 this cause is an ideology to make delhi safe again, to help protect and uplift the women's safety and security in delhi. we need to make this collective measures by volunteering as a team to act upon these things, most importantly get out of social media and do something about it for real. let's make this happen in a vision that every time a man tries to eve tease or do anything wrong, he shall think there's someone doing something about it. looking forward for all your support!

text:
when it comes to sexual harassment questions have been raised over the value of anonymous reporting, for example can action be taken when reports are anonymous? at what point is the identity of the complainant and the accused revealed?
sadly, distrust that complaints will be taken seriously or fear of raising your hand and reporting a grievance prevail. confidential reporting gives voice to the voiceless; after all, harassment is about power remember, so anonymity and self-preservation allows victims to regain some of that control they feel they may have lost.
at tell jane we provide a safe space for employees to report incidences and concerns of workplace harassment confidentially through a freephone hotline manned by experienced hr practitioners.  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
facing the future! from todayâ€™s book trade press:

two deals for alexandra heminsley
news - books thursday, 22 november 2018
non-fiction exploration of the body for chatto and two novels with sphere for grazia books editor and judy murray's ghost

becky hardie at chatto & windus and ed wood at sphere have separately acquired new works of non-fiction and fiction respectively by bestselling author, journalist and broadcaster alexandra heminsley. the deals were simultaneously brokered by sarah ballard at united agents. 
hardie has acquired at auction some body to love by heminsley, a memoir and â€˜biography of her bodyâ€™. according to a statement from ua: 'in the era of #metoo and the gra (gender recognition act), heminsley reconsiders her relationship with her own body as women everywhere do the same. she looks from adolescence to now as mother to the baby boy she is co-parenting with her former partner who is embarking on transition (mtf). how can we learn to best enjoy our bodies without being defined by them? how best to mother a son when what it is to be a woman is being renegotiated so publicly? chatto will publish in early 2021.' hardie said: "we are so happy to welcome alex to chatto for some body to love. she's made a career out of writing honestly and perceptively about her relationship with her body, but this new book promises a whole new level of questioning and understanding. she's such a trusted voice and i can't wait to hear what she has to say." meanwhile wood, editorial director at sphere, has acquired at auction two book club-style novels by heminsley â€“ the first time she has written fiction under her own name. the first, as-yet-untitled debut novel, is an emotional story about two half-sisters that brings nature writing into the fiction arena. sphere will publish in 2021. 
wood said: "with her incisive non-fiction, alex showed how beautifully she could portray our emotional relationship with the natural world through physicality. this book will bring all that talent to an incredibly moving novel of grief, hope and empowerment that will speak to a universal readership. i couldnâ€™t be more proud to be publishing her fiction."

becky hardie at chatto & windus and ed wood at sphere have separately acquired new works of non-fiction and fiction respectively by bestselling author, journalist and broadcaster alexandra heminsley. the deals were simultaneously brokered by sarah ballard at united agents. 
hardie has acquired at auction some body to love by heminsley, a memoir and â€˜biography of her bodyâ€™. according to a statement from ua: 'in the era of  and the gra (gender recognition act), heminsley reconsiders her relationship with her own body as women everywhere do the same. she looks from adolescence to now as mother to the baby boy she is co-parenting with her former paner who is embarking on transition (mtf). how can we learn to best enjoy our bodies without being defined by them? how best to mother a son when what it is to be a woman is being renegotiated so publicly? chatto will publish in early 2021.' hardie said: "we are so happy to welcome alex to chatto for some body to love. she's made a career out of writing honestly and perceptively about her relationship with her body, but this new book promises a whole new level of questioning and understanding. she's such a trusted voice and i can not wait to hear what she has to say." meanwhile wood, editorial director at sphere, has acquired at auction two book club-style novels by heminsley â€“ the first time she has written fiction under her own name. the first, as-yet-untitled debut novel, is an emotional story about two half-sisters that brings nature writing into the fiction arena. sphere will publish in 2021. 
wood said: "with her incisive non-fiction, alex showed how beautifully she could poray our emotional relationship with the natural world through physicality. this book will bring all that talent to an incredibly moving novel of grief, hope and empowerment that will speak to a universal readership. i couldnâ€™t be more proud to be publishing her fiction."

text:
in case you missed it, hereâ€™s a sneak peek into the panel discussion post #foreignbodyplay! it was an intriguing conversation with imogen butler-cole, @priyankabose20 and our very own @dizibot on law, justice & survival.

what counts as justice from the point of view of the survivor? in the light of the latest discussion on the #metoo movement, what does speaking out years after the experience do to the survivor or mean for the survivor? what do we as a society, as individuals listening to the survivor stories, do? how do we ensure support and safe spaces for people to come forward and share their story?

these were only a few questions that were asked, and the answers could perhaps begin to be attempted. #bangalore #pondicherry #ahmedabad #jaipur -- if you want to catch a showing, you can still! more details: www.foreignbodyplay.com

me too, to the goth waif in black skinny jeans.
me too, to the mom with a bob in the van.
me too, to the raven haired surfer with a tan.

me too, to my mother, my aunt and you mister.

what shall we do? 
it happened to them, it can happen to #metoo.
.

text:
women are a tailored version of human beings and men are the untailored version
of it.
that is why they stereotype for boys to have messy rooms and girls to have neater ones, that is why girls are always all time expected to cut out clean.
no feminist move is a wrong move. a common argument made by both feminists and non-feminists alike. 
if 2017 feminists demand to have their tities out in open what's so
wrong about it if men have been doing it for ages. no it's not that we want what men already have. its that
this is a humanly feasible thing and because of our gender we are deprived of it.
why most men are angered from feminism, is because for the first time someone is asking them to tailor their
behaviour accordingly, against their will, and that's again something women have been brought up with so we know
the feeling but men can't take that kind of treatment because they have always been privileged in that sort
of way.
when you go to look into how deep patriarchy is instill in human lives, you might actually get stuck in the swamp of it all. but we must, we must dig deep and look to make the necessary changes.

text:
what constitutes workplace bullying?
bullying isnâ€™t defined in the same way as harassment. primarily, itâ€™s not against the law. bullying tends to be defined as repeated acts of intimidation, hostility and humiliation. but regardless of the legalities, bullying is as devastating to the individual as harassment.
what form does bullying take?
it can include:
verbal abuse, offensive comments
humiliating or ridiculing an individual and belittling their efforts in front of others
deliberate exclusion from conversations, meetings, social events
withholding information that a person needs to fulfil their role
pranks, practical jokes, initiation ceremonies
physical abuse
rifling through, hiding or damaging personal property.  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong

text: you donâ€™t have to call out your relatives if doing so will put you or anyone else in danger. if someone has people who will listen and not hurt them or anyone else, then thatâ€™s one thing and of course we should challenge racism, misogyny, xenophobia, fascism, and all the other very messed up stuff. but i keep running into people who out of guilt and trying to do good by calling out family members are putting themselves (or other loved ones who might be targeted after everyone has left) in danger, because of the mandate weâ€™re hearing to speak up to our families on these holidays. again, if we can, we should! but i also think that this mandate is coming from a very privileged place; that the people who make a blanket call for it perhaps are not understanding what many people have been through in their families. for many, just being around family has fallout. please keep in mind, for example, how many women have families who have refused to believe them that a family member has sexually assaulted or abused them, or who believe but have done nothing about it. for someone facing that, calling someone out may set of a crash into dangerous depression, dorsal vagal collapse, or other debilitating responses that are outside of conscious control. if calling someone out may spark abuse or rage or painful re-igniting of past or present trauma, abuse, neglect, rejection, or pain, then please know you get to chose not to do it. maybe your energy is better spent where it will really do some good, and without putting you in danger. ***or maybe you and the other people around who are awake can decide who the least vulnerable person present is, and that person can be the one ready to call it out.*** but sometimes just getting through the day takes the whole energy. also, you donâ€™t have to go at all if you donâ€™t want to. also, these people on the side of the fascists are 100% always spoiling for a fight, and our words are not going to impact them at all in that setting. so take care. take your words and energy where it will matter. you are not the sacrificial offering. or if you are, take your offering where it will actually matter.

text:
the swedish hacker-cum-vigilante #lisbethsalander aka #thegirlwiththedragontattoo, has been the focus of a number of novels & filmâ€™s thus far, a series which has outlived its original creator #stieglarsson & finds the first novel not to be penned by larsson now the basis of the latest iteration of the character, played once again by a different actorâ€¦ ranking up there with spiderman & sherlock holmes in the recasting stakes, 3 versions in a decade thus far, with woman of the moment #clarefoy the latest actress to take on the grungy titular character.
salander is an interesting creation, certainly in these times of #metoo & the like, a powerful central female icon in a universe that sees almost all the male characters as either powerful yet abusive or weak & very much reliant of salander as their saviour, the one exception to a degree being her hacker accomplice & aideâ€plagueâ€ who very much takes on a sidekick role this time, the dynamic akin to that of batman/alfred or blade/whistler, itâ€™s interesting comparison to draw but one in which the route the studio & writers have taken with the franchise is now beholden to, â€œthe girlâ€ is no longer just an occasional avenging angel with her own issues but a superhero of sorts, indeed the first time we see salander â€œwriting wrongsâ€ the vigilante element that was previously in the periphery has now been well & truly pushed front & centre with the â€œheroâ€ as she has now become being the filmâ€™s primary plotline.
efforts are made to shoe-horn in a more personal connection but it all feels rather unnecessary & desperate as if the film-makers were clinging at straws to be more than just a straightforward thriller, something past filmâ€™s always transcended the boundaries of, particularly #davidfinchers original dragon tattoo remake which was a stylistic marvel with a rather nasty edge & a labyrinthine plot that pulled you in, the male characters were more than mere stereotypes as previously described, here they are nothing other than stereotypes, thinly written ciphers with mikael blomkvist particularly badly served, played last time in a brilliantly vulnerable turn by #danialcraig here his replacement  #sverrirgudnason has

text:
itâ€™s been an incredibly difficult 354 days and i am thankful every single day for the amazing humans that have helped me get back to myself and made sure that i got through these difficult days. in the spirit of thanksgiving, i want to focus on how much i am thankful for all of the amazing humans that have stood by my side after being sexually assaulted. everyone has made a tremendous difference in my life and i donâ€™t want to speculate what even would be my life without every single one of you. and yâ€™all know who you are. you have made a difference in my life for the better, particularly over the last year, and i will never forget every single one of you that has helped me so so so much every single day. today i am especially thankful for you. 
sy, md, rf, om, mt, st, kl: yâ€™all were there from the beginning and continue to be there for me today and iâ€™m so thankful for yâ€™all.
hw, nt, nf, mt: my squad from the other side of the border. yâ€™all have been so so so supportive from hundreds of miles and time zones away. i appreciate the unconditional support for me and the advice that all of you gave me all the time as well. 
js, kk, mb, mt: you were all there for me through the summer. you all have done so much for me and i am thankful for each of you every day.
mt, st, jm: yâ€™all give me confidence every single day that i am doing really well in life and that youâ€™d fight anyone for me. you guys are beyond supportive of everything in my life and iâ€™d be lost without you three. you are the three that i want to run to with anything that i accomplished in life or when things are hard or when i need advice. you have each been so supportive throughout all of the processes that i am looking at. i am so thankful that you have all been there for me on the best days and the worst days and every single day in between. 
i am also so thankful for my fam. they have been supportive in every way that they knew how to. i wish i could be with them today.
i am so thankful for everyone that has been beyond supportive for me. i could not have come all of this way without every single one of you. ğŸ’•

text:
on the way to the trojan wars, the hero philoctetes is abandoned by his fellow warriors because they cannot stand the stink of his infected foot. this myth can be used as a metaphor for what happens when compassion and empathy breaks down for men whose experience of sexual violation seems too terrible for those around them to bear. 
on december 1st in a cpd workshop, sarah van gogh will be in the lab to explore with us the issues related to working therapeutically with men who have experienced any form of sexual violation of abuse. through visualisation, drawing and group sharing we will look at the emotional, psychological and physical consequences, including sexual dysfunction, violent rage, and suicidal depression. all counsellors and therapists welcome. 
#stillpointspaceslondon #malevictims #abuse #metoo #depression #findatherapist #sarahvangogh #counsellors #therapists

text:
this hit me in all the feels today.

i remember fighting my wounds, shaming myself into deeper shame spirals for all that i knew and all that i couldn't undo. 
trauma is real and embodied. it travels with us. we carry it's truth in our bones and it echoes through our spirit.

do not beat yourself up for your scars. your wounds are real and your experiences are valid. 
none of your scars make you less. you are changed.

for the scars that linger below the surface, hidden from sight. i know you. i am you. 
the stones of abuse broke the surface of the water, sending out waves and residual ripple that changed the shoreline... and the stones piled up, forever changing the riverbed of my soul.

the wounds are real. the trauma is real.

i have been changed and shaped through all of this... and as i continued to flow and heal... as i began to stop fighting the wounds and honor them. i began to heal. â€¢â€¢â€¢ i believe you 
i hear you

i see you â€¢â€¢â€¢ i honor the battles you have survived. 
i contend for the healing that is beginning to rise.

you can do this hard, holy work.

@stacie.martin

#wildandholy #wildernessisholy #freerangepastor #ivegotnostringsonme #welcometothenewage #nosurrender #smashthebox #notsorry #riseup #resist #notakebacks #onedayatatime #youarenotthebossofme #believesurvivors #safespaces #metoo

text:
pecunia non olet, il marcio sÃ¬.
prendiamo parola sulla vicenda che in questi giorni sta occupando social e giornali on line, riguardante un noto personaggio del mondo degli eventi musicali a genova: emanuele habanero podestÃ .  accusato da molte e molti di abusi, molestie, violenze e stalking, Ã¨ diventato oggetto di dibattito pubblico solo dopo la rinuncia, motivata pubblicamente, di federico fiumani, a partecipare al supernova festival, avvisato, al pari di moltissimi/e altri/e colleghi/e, delle vicende violente che riguardano podestÃ . diciamo fin da subito che il nostro principale interesse riguarda le molte persone, principalmente donne, che, da anni e non da ieri, subiscono la violenza di questo personaggio. l'hanno detto, ma non sono state ascoltate. sappiamo benissimo cosa significhi raccontare di aver subito molestia, violenza, prevaricazione o stalking e non essere accolte quando lo si racconta, anzi essere sminuite, veder minimizzato quello che di orrendo ti Ã¨ capitato e non essere credute oppure ignorate. se a questo si somma il potere che, in certi ambienti, ha il personaggio in questione, possiamo condividere la paura e la nausea di molte che hanno preferito tacere. anche perchÃ© chi ha parlato pubblicamente, come kants exhibition, mesi fa su fb Ã¨ andata incontro all'oblio, oltre a conseguenze  legali per aver avuto il coraggio di dire la veritÃ . non ci stupiamo di nulla e non pensiamo d'essere migliori di nessuno ma sappiamo quale sia la forza e l'importanza del #metoo e altrettanto siamo consapevoli che per non rimanere sole ad affrontare le conseguenze della propria presa di parola contro la violenza occorre il #wetoogether: la forza di autotutelarci restando le une al fianco delle altre. mettiamo da subito a disposizione tutti i nostri canali social e i nostri spazi di discussione e incontro per accogliere le testimonianze di tutte/i, che siano legate a questa vicenda o che siano legate ad altre situazioni tristemente simili (nonunadimenogenova@gmail.com).

text:
a woman and her three daughters. after dozens of appeals to the police went unanswered, this woman separated from her abusive ex-husband. still, she cannot count on local law enforcement to protect her rights. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for â€œfemicide,â€ the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio. 
#opensociety #argentina #niunamenos #femicide #femicidio #conmisderechosnotemetas #16days #genderbasedviolence #metoo #hearmetoo

text:
a south korean cult leader was convicted on thursday and jailed for 15 years after he raped eight female followers - some of whom believed he was 'god'. pastor lee jaerock set up the manmin central church in guro, seoul, south korea, with just 12 followers in 1982. it grew to 130,000 members, most of whom revered the pastor and believed he was god. as a result, his victims were "unable to resist as they were subject to the accused's absolute religious authority", judge chung moon-sung told the seoul central district court.

but three of lee's followers went public earlier this year, as south korea was swept with a wave of #metoo accusations. the followers who exposed him described how he had summoned each of them to an apartment and raped them.
one of the women who had been a member of the church since childhood told south korean television:

i was unable to turn him down.

he was more than a king. he was god.
lee told another of his victims that she was now in heaven and asked her to strip as adam and eve went naked in the garden of eden.

the woman told jtbc television:

i cried as i hated to do it.
eight women laid criminal complaints but the 75-year-old pastor's lawyers accused the women of lying to seek vengeance after being excommunicated for breaching church rules.

however, the court found lee had raped and molested the women "tens of times" over a long period.

the judge said:

through his sermons the accused has indirectly or directly suggested he is the holy spirit, deifying himself.

the victims believed him to be 'a divine being who wields divine power'
lee denied the charges. as the judgement was read, with around 100 of his followers present in the courtroom, the disgraced pastor stood with his eyes closed and showed no emotion.

he was convicted on thursday, november 22, and jailed for 15 years.
name: Pricilia Baby

text:
my heart is filled with gratitude as i dip my toes in #missionbeach today! 2018 has been a year for deep healing, immense growth, and letting myself fully #beher. 
owning my story and sharing it with the world has been terrifying at times. i'm blessed beyond words to be met with so much kindness and support.

thank you for loving me on this journey!

thank you for believing in my mission!

thank you for showing other #metoo survivors they too are lovable!

i love you!
